    {
      "id": "1248112596213563414",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-06-06T12:13:51.748+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I have tried to make this card work, and not had a lot of success. It really hogs a stasis slot, does very poor frontloaded damage, and then takes a long time to start paying you off. 2 damage per tick is also really slow scaling, even if you can find a way to cheat this into stasis like curl up+ or future plans. Actually paying 3 energy for the initial 18 damage is atrocious, and there are much more powerful things you can use your stasis slots for than this (sentry blast, stasis field, orbwalk+, general card draw+energy generation).\n\nI just don't see why you would ever want to work this hard for scaling damage on guardian. You can socket ruby/onyx into one card and loop it with reroute/recover, you can use resilient plate+ alongside rubies, you can spam 0 cost and stasis with floating orbs, you can use vent steam/garnet to amplify your damage, you have several good multihit attacks to pair with strength gain, you can pair body crash with block spamming and defensive modes blur, you have construction form, and you also have massive card spam strategies using stasis engine. There are no shortage of powerful and effective ways to scale your damage as guardian, and fierce bash is at the absolute bottom of my list as far options go.\n\nI say this a lot, but there are such high opportunity costs associated with being a rare card. They are very expensive at shops (especially after A16), and they are usually seen against 2 other rares from boss card rewards. You really have to stand out and do something special/unique/efficient to compete as a rare, and fierce bash has some incredibly stiff competition, with citrine, onyx, stasis field, gem cannon, stasis engine, spheric shield, exploit gems, compile package, body crash, and bauble burst all being very strong rares in their own ways. I just don't see when you are ever justified in taking this outside of building up rare chance, and even then, if you're past halfway through act 1, you usually won't need clunky damage.",
      "author": {
        "id": "303064746129752074",
        "name": "kiku_katsumi",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Kiku",
        "color": null,
